title: EV makers’ use of Chinese suppliers raises concerns about forced labor
description: Companies with ties to China’s oppressive tactics in Xinjiang are becoming embedded in the EV supply chain, worrying experts who say the industry is at an inflection point on human rights.

title: Trudeau says ‘credible allegations’ tie India to murder in Canada
description: Prime Minister Justin Trudeau told Parliament he has expressed his “deep concerns” about the killing of Hardeep Singh Nijjar to Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi.

title: U.S.-Iran prisoner swap could pave the way for talks on bigger issues
description: The agreement does not address issues beyond the prisoner exchange and release of funds, but the talks could pave the way for negotiations on Iran’s nuclear program.

title: Ukraine ousts more defense officials and decries grain ban by E.U. neighbors
description: Kyiv said it would dispute a ban on grain imports imposed by Poland, Hungary and Slovakia .

title: Biden, at U.N., faces a tough sell on extending support for Ukraine
description: The Russia-Ukraine war’s toll on food and energy prices has accelerated calls in the developing world for a negotiated settlement.

title: Taiwan urges China to stop ‘destructive’ military sorties as tensions mount
description: Beijing is trying to exhaust and intimidate Taiwan’s military with record numbers of  military aircraft and navy vessels detected near the island on Monday.

title: Iran says U.S. prisoner swap moving ahead, showing partial thaw in relations
description: The U.S.-Iran prisoner exchange, which includes a provision to unlock $6 billion in frozen Iranian oil funds, marks a major breakthrough for the bitter foes.

title: Ukraine live briefing: Kyiv says recaptured village opens door to Bakhmut; Zelensky to address U.N., Congress
description: Klishchiivka can serve as a base for offensive action, a military spokesman said, and help Ukraine control logistics routes to Bakhmut, which Russia seized this year.

title: In Wagner’s largest African outpost, Russia looks to tighten its grip
description: After Prigozhin’s death, Wagner mercenaries will still operate in the Central African Republic but under direct control of Russia’s Defense Ministry, officials say.

title: WWII-era letter suggests Vatican knew of Holocaust atrocities
description: A newly uncovered letter from Vatican archives suggests World War II-era Pope Pius XII was aware that thousands of Jews were being killed in Nazi gas chambers.

title: A glimpse of Ukraine’s ruins
description: These photos from a U.S.-supplied Humvee driving along Ukraine’s deserted roads provide a glimpse common in communities along the front lines.
